{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01KegJnUKETwDY6A2Ge1R49h","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Ev36QcZj9LaCpgjvfW4qD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/private/var/folders/pl/c57pb2_52t513h0r4dgr0ryc0000gn/T/exp_2006_A1__forced_path_only__r2_6hm8jxz3/workspace/Solution.lean","content":"import Mathlib\n\nopen MeasureTheory\n\n/-- Putnam 2006 A1.  Find the volume of the region of points `(x, y, z)`\nsuch that `(x² + y² + z² + 8)² ≤ 36 (x² + y²)`.\n\nThe condition is equivalent (after substituting `r = √(x²+y²)`) to\n`(r - 3)² + z² ≤ 1`, a circle of radius `1` centered at `(r, z) = (3, 0)`.\nRevolving it about the `z`-axis gives a torus with revolution radius `3`\nand tube radius `1`, whose volume is, by Pappus,\n`2π · 3 · (π · 1²) = 6π²`. -/\nnoncomputable def putnam_2006_a1_solution : ℝ := 6 * Real.pi ^ 2\n\ntheorem putnam_2006_a1 :\n    (volume {p : Fin 3 → ℝ |\n      ((p 0) ^ 2 + (p 1) ^ 2 + (p 2) ^ 2 + 8) ^ 2 ≤ 36 * ((p 0) ^ 2 + (p 1) ^ 2)}).toReal\n      = putnam_2006_a1_solution := by\n  sorry\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2031,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4598,"cache_read_input_tokens":17308,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4598},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5f5cc1c-2bcd-4fa5-9395-61bc23964e96","uuid":"c0be4ef6-5a0c-464e-a94c-da06782a0553","request_id":"req_011CbatDXXS2kRwpkc9xpbLS"}
